\pard\keepn\sb100\sa100\b\fs36 What Is A WordPress Archive Page\par

\pard\sb100\sa100\b0\fs24 The main purpose of an archive page is to easily navigate your visitor through your previously published content.\par
What exactly a WordPress archive page displays? Archive pages are generated to organize a list of posts under a specific post type, category, or tag. For example, a {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://visualcomposer.com/blog/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul\cf1\cf1\ul blog}}}}\f0\fs24  is a great illustration of the WordPress archive page.\par
Archives are also available for the custom post type. WordPress custom post type is a content type that allows you to add your types of data \i (e.g. custom fields and categories)\i0 . You can create one with a plugin or by adding a custom PHP code into your theme.\par
If your installed theme or plugin supports custom post types \i (e.g. WooCommerce)\i0 , WordPress will automatically create archive pages for your custom post type as well.\par
The archive page has multiple benefits. First of all, it can radically improve SEO and help your audience to find the desired content. Secondly, the archive page is a practical way to display all published pages and different post types. It will ease the navigation process. How? By listing your old content based on a date, category, tags and more.\par
WordPress creates archive pages automatically. So, you don\rquote t need to waste your time making it from scratch. Yet, customization of your archive page can boost your traffic. And better the appearance and the performance of your site. If you want to create a custom archive page, you have several options available. There are a coding and non-coding option. The last one can be using a plugin such as {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://toolset.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul\cf1\cf1\ul Toolset}}}}\f0\fs24 , which lets you build fully custom archive pages.\par

\pard\keepn\sb100\sa100\b\fs36 How to Create an Archive Page in WordPress\par

\pard\sb100\sa100\b0\fs24 Now, you are probably asking the question about how to create an archive page in WordPress? I am going to cover different approaches on how to make your archive page within a few minutes and clicks. You can select and apply the one you like the most.\par

\pard\keepn\sb100\sa100\b\fs28 Theme-Defined Archive Page\par

\pard\sb100\sa100\b0\fs24 Almost every WordPress theme has an integrated file called archive.php. It is used to display and define the archive-type page look. WordPress and theme developers use this file to show the archive\rquote s page input on the front-end.\par
Even though the file is integrated you can still customize the appearance and style it using CSS. Display custom fields in your theme-defined archive page by adding custom PHP code to the archive.php file.\par

\pard\keepn\sb100\sa100\b\fs28 Archive Page Plugins\par

\pard\sb100\sa100\b0\fs24 Plugins make everything easier because most of them utilize shortcodes. Archive page plugins are an alternative solution to the archive page template creation. The plugin is a user-friendly and code-free way to create an archive page.\par
There are a few archive page plugins for WordPress. For example, {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://wordpress.org/plugins/archive-control/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul\cf1\cf1\ul Archive Control}}}}\f0\fs24  and {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://wordpress.org/plugins/anual-archive/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul\cf1\cf1\ul Annual Archive}}}}\f0\fs24 .\par
